00:23.409 --> 00:26.155
WELCOME TO PICO MUNDO

00:26.190 --> 00:27.244
My name is Odd Thomas.

00:27.279 --> 00:31.029
Though in this age when fame is the
altar at which most people worship.

00:31.064 --> 00:32.537
I'm not sure why you should care.

00:32.572 --> 00:34.988
I'm not a celebrity.
I'm not the child of a celebrity.

00:35.023 --> 00:36.777
I've never been married to,
abused by,

00:36.812 --> 00:38.530
or provided a kidney to a celebrity.

00:38.565 --> 00:39.858
Green Moon Bowling

00:42.572 --> 00:46.020
But I do lead an unusual life.

00:53.531 --> 00:55.605
Penny Kalisto.

01:05.615 --> 01:08.080
My name really is Odd.

01:08.115 --> 01:11.488
According to my mother, it was
a screw-up on my birth certificate.

01:11.523 --> 01:14.861
She says I was supposed to be called
Todd, after a Lithuanian uncle.

01:15.282 --> 01:17.539
My father insists my name
was always Odd...

01:17.574 --> 01:20.821
and he notes that all of
my uncles are Bulgarian.

01:21.324 --> 01:24.091
My father claims
my mother is insane.

01:24.126 --> 01:26.860
My mother, of course,
begs to differ.

01:27.575 --> 01:32.777
My abilities are a gift from God!

01:33.533 --> 01:35.489
My father won that argument.

01:36.742 --> 01:40.403
I was 12 years old when they finally
locked her up and threw away the key.

01:45.409 --> 01:49.569
I've come to believe that
my mother and I share certain...

01:49.659 --> 01:51.082
abilities.

01:51.117 --> 01:53.826
Since I don't want to be locked up
with the key thrown away...

01:53.861 --> 01:57.985
I've pretty much kept mine a secret.

02:05.909 --> 02:07.368
Odd Thomas.

02:07.403 --> 02:08.792
Hello, Harlo.

02:08.827 --> 02:10.375
Long time, no see.

02:10.410 --> 02:13.327
Whoa! Whoa! Hey, hey.
Come on, man. No touchy, no feely.

02:13.362 --> 02:16.401
- Sorry, but I love this car.
- I know.

02:16.436 --> 02:19.440
It's too bad a car
can't love you back.

02:22.077 --> 02:24.304
What's wrong, Odd?
There anything I can do?

02:24.339 --> 02:26.531
No, it's something
you've already done.

02:27.369 --> 02:29.509
Hey! Hey! Come on- oh, Odd.
No fooling around, man.

02:29.544 --> 02:31.650
- Give me my keys.
- Her blood is in your pocket.

02:33.620 --> 02:35.866
Most people would think
that's a weird thing to say...

02:35.901 --> 02:38.113
but you don't think
it's very weird, do you, Harlo?

02:44.995 --> 02:46.239
On that night...

02:47.704 --> 02:50.204
you took a piece of white felt...

02:50.239 --> 02:52.127
and after killing Penny...

02:52.162 --> 02:54.870
you collected some of her blood.

02:54.905 --> 02:56.919
And now it's dry...

02:56.954 --> 03:00.700
and stiff and
brittle like a cracker...

03:01.538 --> 03:05.283
and it's still in your pocket.

03:12.996 --> 03:15.705
In moments like these,
pity tears at me.

03:15.740 --> 03:18.379
And a kind of madness
comes over me...

03:18.414 --> 03:21.122
forcing me to hunt people
like Harlo Landerson...

03:21.157 --> 03:25.068
who I have no pity for whatsoever.

03:42.373 --> 03:44.448
Sorry, Mrs. Curtees!

03:46.332 --> 03:47.908
Sorry, Saleen!

04:21.250 --> 04:23.000
What the hell are you doing?

04:23.035 --> 04:25.205
Mom, what's going on?

04:29.459 --> 04:31.331
Stevie, run honey, run!

04:39.876 --> 04:40.906
Come here!

04:49.793 --> 04:52.496
My life is filled with guys
like Harlo Landerson.

04:55.835 --> 04:58.122
And since I like my face
just the way it is...

04:59.378 --> 05:01.036
I learned how to handle myself.

05:17.795 --> 05:22.287
I may see dead people, but then,
by God, I do something about it.

05:23.129 --> 05:24.969
Hey. Hey!

05:25.004 --> 05:26.927
Shift down, man! Go easy.

05:26.962 --> 05:29.877
I'm sorry, sir,
but I don't have a "go easy" gear.

05:31.046 --> 05:32.796
You should probably get that looked at.

05:32.831 --> 05:34.345
Now, Officer Eckles...

05:34.380 --> 05:35.470
does being a police officer

05:35.505 --> 05:37.171
give you the right to beat
the shit out of people?

05:37.206 --> 05:38.803
Not at all, Officer Varner.

05:38.838 --> 05:40.828
But it is one of
the perks of the job.

05:46.880 --> 05:51.039
I believe in a higher power
and the afterlife.

05:52.713 --> 05:54.586
Call me strange.

05:55.631 --> 05:56.845
Others do.

05:56.880 --> 05:58.752
He's so strange.

06:01.131 --> 06:02.471
Don't worry, Penny.

06:02.506 --> 06:05.922
I think where you're going
is a home for the spirit...

06:05.957 --> 06:09.585
and it's filled with
kindness and wonder.

06:10.714 --> 06:12.587
I'm sorry, Penny.

06:13.131 --> 06:15.702
I'm sorry your life was so short.

06:26.257 --> 06:27.915
The dead don't talk.

06:28.757 --> 06:30.831
I don't know why.

06:35.425 --> 06:36.722
Here we are again.

06:36.757 --> 06:40.005
Busted furniture and
shattered glass everywhere.

06:41.966 --> 06:44.015
Most of it was not my fault.

06:44.050 --> 06:47.446
Except the panda bear lamp
and the Biffy the Clown mirror.

06:47.481 --> 06:50.806
- That was this guy.
- Why didn't you come to me first..

06:50.841 --> 06:54.675
give me a chance to find a way
to get Harlo to entrap himself?

06:54.710 --> 06:55.807
Whenever we do it that way,

06:55.842 --> 06:57.967
it's always more efficient
and less destructive.

06:58.002 --> 07:00.092
Yes, I know but he had
to be stopped right now...

07:00.127 --> 07:02.297
or he was gonna do it again soon.

07:02.800 --> 07:05.510
That's what Penny wanted to tell me.
That's why she hadn't left yet.

07:05.545 --> 07:08.957
Son, you so complicate my life.

07:11.759 --> 07:13.003
Look.

07:14.801 --> 07:15.891
Besides her blood...

07:15.926 --> 07:19.885
Harlo had these photos of Penny
post-mortem in his wallet.

07:19.920 --> 07:22.673
If there's any fuss about
how you pegged Harlo...

07:22.708 --> 07:25.427
just say he opened up
his wallet to pay off a bet.

07:25.462 --> 07:28.219
Five bucks on
yesterday's Dodger's game...

07:28.254 --> 07:30.377
the photos fell out,
you saw em-

07:30.412 --> 07:32.500
He ran and naturally,
I gave chase.

07:33.136 --> 07:34.380
Naturally.

08:24.389 --> 08:28.076
Save me!

08:28.111 --> 08:31.729
Save us!

08:31.764 --> 08:33.701
- Save
- Us!

08:33.736 --> 08:35.623
- Save..
- Us!

08:35.658 --> 08:37.510
Save you from who?

08:40.097 --> 08:41.342
Who is that?

08:42.390 --> 08:43.763
Who is it?

09:21.558 --> 09:23.134
Evil is coming.

09:23.641 --> 09:26.889
And it's up to me to figure out
who's gonna be holding the gun.

09:27.933 --> 09:29.391
Morning, Elvis.

09:30.226 --> 09:31.107
Pico Mundo Grill
CLOSED

09:31.142 --> 09:32.774
So much of my life
is out of my controI.

09:32.809 --> 09:36.351
I would have gone 7 kinds of
crazy if I hadn't simplified.

09:36.386 --> 09:40.018
So I have no motorized vehicles,
no homeownership...

09:40.053 --> 09:43.018
no insurance,
and no grand ambitions.

09:43.053 --> 09:44.179
Ladies.

09:44.601 --> 09:46.108
Eggs! Wreck em and stretch em!

09:46.143 --> 09:48.768
"Wreck em" means scrambled,
and "stretch em" means...

09:48.803 --> 09:49.983
add an extra egg.

09:50.018 --> 09:51.441
Cardiac shingles and hash browns!

09:51.476 --> 09:54.601
"Cardiac shingles"
are toast with lots of butter.

09:54.636 --> 09:56.328
And hash browns...

09:56.363 --> 09:57.984
are just hash browns.

09:58.019 --> 10:00.720
Not every word
we use is diner lingo.

10:02.102 --> 10:03.608
Just as not every short-order cook

10:03.643 --> 10:07.811
is an undercover detective
for dead people.

10:07.846 --> 10:09.268
Duck.

10:15.311 --> 10:18.609
That is Stormy Lewellyn.

10:18.644 --> 10:23.137
Stormy and I are destined
to be together forever.

10:25.103 --> 10:26.477
GYPSY MUMMY ALL SEEING EYE

10:27.394 --> 10:31.554
You are destined
to be together forever.

10:34.478 --> 10:37.098
Hey, Chief.
Tummy Tickler coming at ya.

10:41.146 --> 10:43.562
You know, I'm still not happy
about what you did yesterday, Oddie.

10:43.597 --> 10:44.813
You could have
gotten yourself killed.

10:44.848 --> 10:47.486
I am not afraid of death.

10:47.521 --> 10:50.010
Of course, I'm not ready to go
on a date with him, either.

10:56.479 --> 10:58.147
Would you throw yourself
off a cliff for me?

10:58.182 --> 10:59.029
Of course I would.

10:59.064 --> 11:01.897
Into a river of razor blades
and lemon juice?

11:01.932 --> 11:03.112
Absolutely.

11:03.147 --> 11:05.522
Of course, I'd like to know
the reasoning behind such a request..

11:05.557 --> 11:07.570
but, fortunately for me...

11:07.605 --> 11:10.939
you reek of intelligence
and integrity.

11:10.974 --> 11:13.231
And you reek of peach shampoo.

11:13.266 --> 11:15.636
Just the way I like you.

11:16.898 --> 11:19.030
- Chief.
- Morning, Stormy.

11:19.065 --> 11:21.356
What's with
the cat-ate-the-canary smile?

11:21.391 --> 11:23.229
Tonight is date night.

11:23.981 --> 11:26.268
So you think you're
gonna get yourself some, huh?

11:26.565 --> 11:29.606
- I wouldn't put it quite that way.
- Stormy SpeciaI.

11:29.641 --> 11:31.681
- Girlfriend.
- Morning, dude.

11:49.607 --> 11:51.240
I call them bodachs.

11:51.275 --> 11:52.906
Well, not to their faces, I hope.

11:52.941 --> 11:55.311
I never met anybody
that could see em before.

11:55.524 --> 11:58.234
- Neither have I.
- Everyone told me it's in my head.

11:58.269 --> 11:59.817
Well, you should stop
telling everyone.

11:59.852 --> 12:01.448
I tried telling my parents.

12:01.483 --> 12:03.025
If I told my parents,
I'd ve spent my whole life...

12:03.060 --> 12:04.916
picking winning lottery numbers.

12:04.951 --> 12:06.772
You can pick winning lotto numbers?

12:07.192 --> 12:10.026
- No, I can't. Stay on point.
- Right. Yeah.

12:10.061 --> 12:13.151
Yesterday, when I finally saw one...

12:13.186 --> 12:15.317
I gave him the finger, Homes.

12:15.352 --> 12:16.741
Don't you know?

12:16.776 --> 12:20.307
If they find out you can see them,
they will kill you.

12:26.985 --> 12:28.561
They will kill you.

13:04.695 --> 13:06.326
- Little advice?
- Yeah?

13:06.361 --> 13:08.327
Karla prefers chocolate to flowers

13:08.362 --> 13:10.862
and you should get
yourself some candles.

13:10.897 --> 13:11.892
Candles?

13:12.403 --> 13:13.980
Thanks. Good idea.

13:19.612 --> 13:21.244
Whew, close.

13:21.279 --> 13:22.946
That would have been
a little awkward.

13:22.981 --> 13:25.400
You two are really something.

13:25.435 --> 13:27.786
I don't know what, but something.

13:27.821 --> 13:30.321
We're weird and screwed up
but we're okay.

13:30.356 --> 13:31.565
I don't know.

13:31.780 --> 13:33.237
You are...

13:34.405 --> 13:35.703
so cool.

13:35.738 --> 13:39.405
So, you deny me my weirdness,
but agree that I'm screwed up?

13:39.440 --> 13:41.037
You're right.
I see your problem.

13:41.072 --> 13:43.363
Weirdness, it can be fun.
It can be kind of cooI.

13:43.398 --> 13:47.114
Screwed-up-ness, not so much.

13:47.149 --> 13:49.899
You are quite weird.

13:51.489 --> 13:54.698
- Apology accepted.
- I gotta go. Be good, you two.

13:54.733 --> 13:57.322
It's not me you have to worry about.

13:57.357 --> 13:58.650
Don't I know it.

13:59.281 --> 14:01.490
I gotta go to work, too, Oddie.

14:01.525 --> 14:03.776
- Okay.
- Later, my love.

14:14.490 --> 14:15.652
Stormy!

14:24.407 --> 14:26.149
Miss you already.

14:31.075 --> 14:32.825
- Living up to his name.
- Every damn day.

14:32.860 --> 14:34.069
Later.

14:34.491 --> 14:38.241
Months often pass
when I don't see a single bodach.

14:38.276 --> 14:39.165
When they do show up...

14:39.200 --> 14:42.325
it's a sure sign that carnage
and bloodshed are not far behind.

14:42.360 --> 14:43.207
Morning.

14:43.242 --> 14:45.446
They don't cause it.
They feed on it.

14:46.076 --> 14:49.690
The more bodachs that show up,
the bigger the eventuaI feast.

14:52.117 --> 14:54.617
They're attracted to evil
like bees to flowers.

14:54.652 --> 14:57.117
They know when death is coming
and want to watch.

14:57.152 --> 14:59.458
They don't show up
for any ordinary death.

14:59.493 --> 15:03.783
They want extreme,
operatic violence and terror.

15:05.952 --> 15:08.869
Penny Kalisto's death
wasn't horrific enough...

15:08.904 --> 15:12.613
to bring a single bodach
into our world.

15:16.078 --> 15:19.277
This town is in serious trouble.

15:20.452 --> 15:22.536
- Bye, Oddie.
- See you, ladies.

15:22.571 --> 15:24.408
Nicolina! Levanna!

15:28.244 --> 15:30.947
Odd, am I really sucking
at this whole "mother" thing?

15:32.411 --> 15:34.460
Well, considering their
last one was a junkie...

15:34.495 --> 15:37.119
who left them in your lap
when you were barely 18...

15:37.154 --> 15:40.745
I think you rather rock, Vi.

15:40.780 --> 15:41.775
See you later.

15:42.328 --> 15:44.252
I'm heading this way, too.

15:44.287 --> 15:46.641
Gonna go see Madame Pearl,
get myself read.

15:46.676 --> 15:48.961
Personally,
I don't believe people who say...

15:48.996 --> 15:52.120
they can read minds or palms
and, trust me, tea leaves...

15:52.155 --> 15:53.836
just cloggage
in the garbage disposal.

15:53.871 --> 15:56.913
It's just I had this dream
last night you would not believe.

15:56.948 --> 16:00.663
Well, anything short of
a 9-alarm massacre, I can top.

16:00.698 --> 16:03.365
I'd never seen myself face-on
in a dream before.

16:04.705 --> 16:06.128
You saw your own face?

16:06.163 --> 16:09.705
Me and this guy, we were
both lying dead all busted up...

16:09.740 --> 16:12.407
like we'd been shot
to pieces or something.

16:17.622 --> 16:19.796
You know, I wouldn't worry
about it, Vi.

16:19.831 --> 16:21.905
I mean, have any of
your dreams ever come true?

16:22.831 --> 16:23.993
No.

16:24.622 --> 16:27.331
I know most people think
you're just quirky or weird, Odd...

16:27.366 --> 16:29.414
except Stormy who thinks
angels fly out of your butt.

16:29.449 --> 16:31.164
But I know there's more to it.

16:31.199 --> 16:32.713
You have a secret.

16:32.748 --> 16:34.671
You're either a clairvoyant...

16:34.706 --> 16:36.964
a psychic, a seer,
a soothsayer, or something.

16:36.999 --> 16:39.206
Or you got yourself some juice
with a higher power.

16:39.241 --> 16:40.088
And I need to know.

16:40.123 --> 16:41.996
Tell me the truth now, Odd.

16:42.832 --> 16:44.906
Do you see death in me?

16:48.165 --> 16:52.624
No. No, all I see
is my own insensitivity...

16:52.659 --> 16:56.072
and a long,
happy life for you, okay?

16:59.916 --> 17:03.661
Hey, Vi, the the dead guy
in your dream, what was he wearing?

17:04.415 --> 17:06.374
Wearing? I don't know.

17:06.409 --> 17:08.632
Oh! Wait. Yeah...

17:08.666 --> 17:13.157
a red and black shirt with
black bowling balls on it.

17:19.916 --> 17:22.959
One of my stranger abilities is
that when I need to find someone...

17:22.992 --> 17:25.507
like right now, the creepy
guy in the diner,

17:25.541 --> 17:29.501
I can randomly wander around, and
pretty quickly, I'll run into him.

17:29.536 --> 17:31.907
This is a talent for
which I have no name.

17:32.209 --> 17:35.126
Stormy calls it psychic magnetism.

17:35.161 --> 17:37.717
TIRE WORLD
Super Summer Sale

17:37.752 --> 17:40.633
That's Tom Jedd.
He was my little league coach.

17:40.668 --> 17:44.835
Been hanging around Tire World for
years, although I don't know why.

17:44.870 --> 17:47.210
His death was not caused
by a defective tire.

17:47.245 --> 17:50.955
Such a beautifuI girl-

17:56.794 --> 18:00.461
There is something about
a dead man trying to get a laugh...

18:00.496 --> 18:02.535
that just bugs me.

18:03.586 --> 18:06.919
Perhaps because it suggests
that even in death...

18:06.954 --> 18:09.835
we still have a pathetic
need to be liked.

18:10.044 --> 18:14.418
As well as the ever-present
ability to humiliate ourselves.

18:17.211 --> 18:18.788
Where are you?

18:20.337 --> 18:22.624
Where are you?

18:26.379 --> 18:27.327
MANAGER Stormy

18:32.755 --> 18:36.588
When I finally have my own shop,
no stupid uniforms.

18:36.623 --> 18:39.088
I think you look adorable.

18:39.123 --> 18:41.038
Adorable? Really?

18:41.073 --> 18:42.953
Puppies are adorable.

18:44.004 --> 18:46.817
Why are you here so early?
You missing me?

18:46.852 --> 18:49.630
Always.
But I'm here looking for a guy.

18:49.665 --> 18:50.429
A creepy guy.

18:50.464 --> 18:54.214
Well, with you,
there can be no other kind.

18:54.249 --> 18:57.745
My psychic magnetism
brought me here.

19:04.423 --> 19:07.337
- That guy?
- That guy.

19:08.465 --> 19:10.715
You are better than a bloodhound.

19:10.750 --> 19:12.964
What is that thing on his head?

19:12.999 --> 19:13.971
Hair.

19:14.006 --> 19:15.964
It looks like a yellow yarmulke.

19:15.999 --> 19:17.597
No, it's hair.

19:17.632 --> 19:19.982
Any of those bodachs with him?

19:20.017 --> 19:22.334
More than I've ever seen before.

19:26.299 --> 19:28.788
You're not shivering
'cause of cold ice cream, are you?

19:31.716 --> 19:33.902
I'm gonna see what this guy's up to.

19:33.937 --> 19:36.090
- Stormy, wait, wait.
- You, sit.

19:45.675 --> 19:47.961
You think those fish
are up to something?

19:48.383 --> 19:51.717
All fish do are eat, excrete,
and fornicate all in the same water.

19:51.752 --> 19:53.140
Fish are disgusting.

19:53.175 --> 19:55.307
Oh, I never thought so till now.

19:55.342 --> 19:58.175
Your creepy friend is buying
two gallons of the summer special.

19:58.210 --> 19:59.599
Are the flavors significant?

19:59.634 --> 20:02.122
That's your department.
I'm just reporting in.

20:02.426 --> 20:04.572
Cherry chocolate coconut chunk?

20:04.607 --> 20:06.683
Coconut cherry chocolate chunk.

20:06.718 --> 20:11.176
I didn't realize the grammar was
so rigid in the ice-cream business.

20:11.211 --> 20:12.550
Well, now you know.

20:16.718 --> 20:18.590
This is bad for business.

20:19.843 --> 20:21.999
Why? No one can see em but me.

20:24.926 --> 20:27.172
Well, how could a bunch
of slithering, evil spirits...

20:27.207 --> 20:29.419
and guy who look like
fungus be good for business?

20:30.052 --> 20:32.541
Fungus Man scares me.
Can't you forget him?

20:32.969 --> 20:33.850
I have a gift.

20:33.885 --> 20:36.177
It wouldn't have been given to me
if I wasn't supposed to use it.

20:36.212 --> 20:38.261
- Maybe it's not a gift.
- It's a gift.

20:38.296 --> 20:40.548
I still got the box it came in.

20:41.595 --> 20:42.727
Here. Take my keys.

20:42.762 --> 20:44.880
And please show up
for dinner alive...

20:44.915 --> 20:46.999
because, remember,
I can't see the dead.

21:22.763 --> 21:25.437
If someone is going
to cause extreme violence...

21:25.472 --> 21:29.270
especially on a massive scale,
which this is starting to look like...

21:29.305 --> 21:34.009
bodachs will not leave him untiI the
last ounce of blood has been spilled.

21:35.556 --> 21:38.589
But they lost interest
in Fungus Man.

22:17.350 --> 22:20.350
Winstons, Camels, and Marlboros.

22:20.385 --> 22:23.265
Fungus Man has friends.

23:03.060 --> 23:05.051
Oh, now would be
a good time to run.

24:34.023 --> 24:35.054
Bodachs.

26:14.737 --> 26:17.356
- Hey.
- Loop me in, odd one.

26:17.654 --> 26:21.612
I think I just achieved a personaI
best in the "jump and gasp" event.

26:21.647 --> 26:23.504
Don't be such a scaredy-cat.

26:23.539 --> 26:25.328
I found a gateway to hell.

26:25.363 --> 26:26.911
I'm walking back to it right now.

26:26.946 --> 26:29.738
