I supposed to listen with?

32:49.758 --> 32:52.383
Right. My heart.
I'm supposed to listen with my heart.

32:52.418 --> 32:53.599
Listen with my heart.

32:53.634 --> 32:58.842
I will do something big
to improve our financial situation.

32:58.877 --> 33:00.766
- Your idea about selling car tires?
- Bigger.

33:00.801 --> 33:03.092
And what, from your perspective,
is bigger than tires?

33:03.127 --> 33:04.109
- Shoes.
- Shoes?

33:04.144 --> 33:05.057
Yeah, think about it.

33:05.092 --> 33:07.738
A family of 5 might have 2 cars
but they have 10 feet.

33:07.773 --> 33:10.349
Not only that, but they need
different kinds of shoes.

33:10.384 --> 33:12.676
Dress shoes, winkle pickers,
high-tops, low-tops, running shoes-

33:12.711 --> 33:14.760
But not you. You have
5 pairs of the same sneakers.

33:14.795 --> 33:16.964
- Like I said
- You're not like most people.

33:17.885 --> 33:20.089
Not in the least.

33:28.302 --> 33:29.969
Do you want crackers
with your cheese?

33:30.003 --> 33:31.184
We have a problem.

33:31.219 --> 33:32.886
Crackers aren't a problem,
just a choice.

33:32.921 --> 33:33.684
- Come on.
- What?

33:33.719 --> 33:35.591
- Come on! It's Fungus Bob!
- What!

33:36.844 --> 33:38.716
He followed me. I don't know how.

33:39.886 --> 33:43.184
Shit! Come on! Come on!

33:43.219 --> 33:44.852
- It's him? You're sure?
- Sure, I'm sure!

33:44.887 --> 33:47.386
You don't think the two of us
could kick his ass?

33:47.421 --> 33:48.927
Not this guy.

34:10.804 --> 34:12.261
- Come on!
- The sacristy!

34:17.804 --> 34:19.879
The back door.
Come on. Come on.

34:20.179 --> 34:21.937
Wait! Wait. Come here.

34:21.971 --> 34:24.674
We're heading towards danger,
not away from it. I can feeI it.

34:26.138 --> 34:28.922
It's like he's everywhere.
He's in front of us. He's behind us.

34:29.971 --> 34:31.429
Come on.
Let's go back the way we came.

34:31.465 --> 34:33.382
- Let's call the cops.
- No time.

34:33.418 --> 34:35.302
I have a better plan.
You stay here.

34:35.723 --> 34:37.284
I'm gonna run over there
and open the door.

34:37.320 --> 34:38.848
If he doesn't lunge through,
you run that way.

34:38.882 --> 34:40.978
If, however, he does lunge through,

34:41.014 --> 34:43.097
you run this way and
I'll try to follow you.

34:43.132 --> 34:44.632
Some plan, odd one.

34:44.668 --> 34:46.132
It's the best I've got.

34:46.556 --> 34:48.097
Full of stuffin'.

35:02.265 --> 35:04.973
Does that mean "Get on with it"
or "Up yours"?

35:05.008 --> 35:06.431
Unbelievable.

35:06.973 --> 35:08.004
Right.

35:44.976 --> 35:46.552
Come on! Come on!

36:01.352 --> 36:02.567
Chief, it's Stormy.

36:02.602 --> 36:05.310
I'm sorry to drop in on date night,
but here's Odd.

36:05.345 --> 36:07.983
Sir, if you send a car real
quick to St. Bart's...

36:08.018 --> 36:10.728
you may be able to catch
Robertson trashing the sacristy...

36:10.763 --> 36:11.942
or even the whole church.

36:11.977 --> 36:14.026
What was he doing
vandalizing St. Bart's?

36:14.061 --> 36:16.561
He was trying to catch me
and Stormy in the belfry.

36:16.596 --> 36:18.520
What were you and Stormy
doing in the belfry?

36:18.555 --> 36:20.682
Well, we were having a picnic, sir.

36:20.717 --> 36:22.810
I'm sure that makes sense to you.

36:25.395 --> 36:28.889
My guy at Robertsons house said
he still hasn't been home yet.

36:28.924 --> 36:32.385
Yeah, because apparently
Bob's been too busy following me.

36:33.228 --> 36:34.319
Oh, one second.

36:34.354 --> 36:36.646
- Where are you going?
- To get some food.

36:36.681 --> 36:38.937
How can you think
of dinner right now?

36:38.972 --> 36:40.778
Because I'm hungry.

36:40.812 --> 36:43.727
Look, Odd.
Vandalism, big deaI.

36:44.146 --> 36:47.643
I thought you said this guy
was gonna bring on the apocalypse.

36:47.678 --> 36:51.139
Yes, sir, on August 15th,
which is less than 3 hours away.

36:51.229 --> 36:54.346
Trust me, that is the day that
Pico Mundo will never forget.

36:57.063 --> 36:58.487
Lyle!

36:58.522 --> 37:00.668
Oh. Hi, Odd. Hi Stormy.

37:00.703 --> 37:02.813
- Hi, Ozzie.
- Hey, Oz.

37:02.848 --> 37:04.271
Odd.

37:05.813 --> 37:06.772
- I'll be right back.
- Lyle, you know that

37:07.611 --> 37:08.641
I know guys who know guys, right?
Right. - Right.

37:08.676 --> 37:11.564
So if you guys don't stop
messing up my takeout orders..

37:11.599 --> 37:13.314
you're the one that's gonna
get taken out. Get it?

37:13.349 --> 37:14.321
- Got it.
- Good.

37:14.356 --> 37:16.439
Oz, Oz, watch your blood pressure.

37:16.474 --> 37:18.071
My blood- Hey, Odd...

37:18.106 --> 37:19.897
my blood has got
cholesterol molecules

37:19.932 --> 37:21.196
the size of marshmallows in it...

37:21.231 --> 37:23.648
and if it wasn't for a little
righteous outrage every now and again

37:23.683 --> 37:25.722
my arteries would
completely collapse.

37:28.106 --> 37:31.649
I finished that
trinket you asked for.

37:31.684 --> 37:33.639
Perfect.

37:37.065 --> 37:39.322
Wow, Oz, what exactly is this?

37:39.357 --> 37:43.024
It's a steel heart 6 inches
in diameter, like you said.

37:43.059 --> 37:44.448
No, I said...

37:44.483 --> 37:48.107
"A piece of steel 6 inches
in diameter to go over a heart. "

37:48.142 --> 37:50.608
Well, man,
I embellished, you know?

37:50.643 --> 37:52.156
I get in the moment.

37:52.191 --> 37:54.774
I mean, why would Stormy
wanna wear that?

37:54.809 --> 37:56.615
It's not for Stormy.

37:56.650 --> 37:59.896
I keep having this image of a...

38:02.400 --> 38:04.474
a bullet going through a heart.

38:07.400 --> 38:09.557
It's perfect. Thank you.

38:13.526 --> 38:14.556
Hey, Chief.

38:17.192 --> 38:20.109
- This place is trashed.
- Yeah, it was Bob Robertson, sir.

38:20.144 --> 38:21.949
I'm sure you're right.
You always are.

38:21.984 --> 38:25.193
But he was long gone.
Didn't leave a single print.

38:25.228 --> 38:27.485
Even the chalices were spotless.

38:27.520 --> 38:28.408
Weird, huh?

38:28.443 --> 38:32.068
I'll give my psychic magnetism a try
to see if I can find him again.

38:32.103 --> 38:33.408
Take Stormy home first.

38:33.443 --> 38:35.318
- Like hell he will!
- I heard that.

38:35.353 --> 38:36.432
He heard that.

38:36.860 --> 38:39.325
Chief, you know
I love Oddie desperately...

38:39.360 --> 38:43.527
so madly I would cut off my hand if
that made any sense as proof of love.

38:43.562 --> 38:45.528
And now I find out
there's a guy trying to kill him.

38:45.563 --> 38:47.813
No one was trying
to kill me, Stormy.

38:48.236 --> 38:50.076
What, you think
he was hitting on you?

38:50.111 --> 38:53.445
You know, this is the craziest
conversation I've ever had.

38:53.480 --> 38:55.944
Odd you're a fountain
of crazy conversations.

38:55.979 --> 38:57.272
A geyser.

38:59.278 --> 39:02.399
Time feels like
a powerfuI black wave...

39:02.434 --> 39:05.520
