Fungus Bob's car anywhere.

39:43.655 --> 39:45.406
You think the slaughter of
the bowling alley people

39:45.441 --> 39:46.780
and Fungus Bob are connected?

39:46.815 --> 39:48.108
Yeah.

39:49.364 --> 39:51.236
Yeah, yeah, I know they are.

39:57.281 --> 39:58.939
GREEN MOON BOWLING

40:14.157 --> 40:15.946
They got new uniforms.

40:27.616 --> 40:29.157
Don't you dare.

40:29.574 --> 40:31.447
Oh, Wyatt.

40:32.408 --> 40:36.242
You said that whatever was gonna
happen wouldn't happen untiI tomorrow.

40:36.277 --> 40:38.551
- Yes, sir, but you see-
- I still got an hour.

40:38.585 --> 40:40.825
I know, sir.
I just want to keep you up to date.

40:40.860 --> 40:42.457
I think there's a good chance that

40:42.492 --> 40:44.632
Bob Robertson might
come to Green Moon Alley...

40:44.667 --> 40:46.774
to do a little more
than just hook some balls.

40:56.243 --> 40:59.285
Maybe you wanna send a guy out here
to, you know, keep an eye out?

40:59.320 --> 41:01.417
Any of those bodarch things around?

41:01.452 --> 41:05.610
Bodachs. No, sir,
but they will show up when he does.

41:05.743 --> 41:08.446
Yeah-yeah. All right.
I'll send a guy right over.

41:10.202 --> 41:11.991
Something doesn't feel right.

41:12.410 --> 41:13.833
Something's wrong.

41:13.868 --> 41:15.431
Are you nuts?
Everything's wrong.

41:15.466 --> 41:16.959
There's going to be a massacre...

41:16.994 --> 41:18.973
and I'll bet you
it's going to happen here.

41:19.008 --> 41:20.917
No, all we know is it's
the same uniforms,

41:20.952 --> 41:23.451
so it's the same
group of people getting killed.

41:23.486 --> 41:25.950
But tomorrow,
any of them could be anywhere.

41:28.661 --> 41:31.991
God, I'm missing something.
I'm missing a piece of the puzzle.

41:35.120 --> 41:36.778
I need to see Viola.

41:39.786 --> 41:40.948
Evening!

41:41.870 --> 41:44.162
- Odd Thomas, right?
- Yeah.

41:44.197 --> 41:45.430
Miss Lewellyn.

41:45.465 --> 41:46.627
The chief sent me.

41:46.662 --> 41:49.281
So you know this guy, right?

41:50.329 --> 41:53.327
I've seen him a couple times today
but no, I don't know him.

41:53.537 --> 41:56.371
Yeah, chief says,
If you see him reach for his pocket

41:56.406 --> 41:58.243
he's probably not going
for a breath mint.

41:59.704 --> 42:01.627
- Wise words from a wise man.
- Yeah.

42:01.662 --> 42:04.779
So what exactly makes this guy
so suspicious and dangerous?

42:05.205 --> 42:07.823
He came into the grill
for lunch today.

42:08.871 --> 42:11.158
That's it? You served him lunch?

42:11.193 --> 42:13.446
- He was weird.
- How weird?

42:13.538 --> 42:14.545
He had weird friends.

42:14.580 --> 42:16.039
- He has friends?
- Weird ones.

42:16.074 --> 42:17.413
How weird?

42:18.039 --> 42:19.283
Very weird.

42:22.289 --> 42:26.664
And a couple hours ago,
he got very aggressive with me.

42:26.699 --> 42:28.629
Wait. A couple hours ago,

42:28.664 --> 42:32.077
this guy, Bob Robertson
got aggressive with you?

42:32.831 --> 42:35.415
Look, the creep made a pass at me
and Odd told him to back off...

42:35.449 --> 42:38.247
and the creep got,
you know, creepy.

42:39.081 --> 42:40.326
Creepy.

42:42.831 --> 42:45.623
Hey, Simon, I've been dying
to know what this tattoo means.

42:45.658 --> 42:47.282
- Do you mind?
- POD

42:49.082 --> 42:51.037
Well, Stormy...

42:51.249 --> 42:53.505
when I was a teenager,
I was a mess.

42:53.540 --> 42:56.519
If it wasn't for the police
academy and the good Lord

42:56.554 --> 42:59.499
Let's just say this tattoo
is a crude obscenity...

42:59.534 --> 43:01.454
that I'd rather not
say the meaning of.

43:01.791 --> 43:04.575
Well, what a gentleman you are.

43:07.000 --> 43:08.540
Nighty-night, Simon.

43:09.292 --> 43:10.535
Night.

43:14.167 --> 43:15.715
You manipulate me like that?

43:15.750 --> 43:18.334
Good heavens odd one,
I manipulate you every day.

43:18.369 --> 43:19.673
- You do?
- Yes.

43:19.708 --> 43:22.625
Gently, of course, and with great
affection and you always like it.

43:22.660 --> 43:23.869
Oh, I do?

43:24.292 --> 43:26.549
You are so adorable.

43:26.584 --> 43:28.716
- I'm not adorable.
- Oh, please.

43:28.751 --> 43:31.459
Puppies, puppies,
little puppies, are adorable.

43:31.494 --> 43:35.618
You and puppies,
totally adorable.

43:38.542 --> 43:40.533
I had a feeling
I'd see you tonight.

43:41.168 --> 43:43.459
- It's about my dream, isn't it?
- You said you were shot.

43:43.494 --> 43:47.259
My skull was all whacked,
my eyeball swollen.

43:47.294 --> 43:49.856
You know dreams have nothing
to do with the reaI future, Vi.

43:49.891 --> 43:52.418
We've already been over that
territory, but here you are.

43:52.453 --> 43:54.077
Where are you in your dream?

43:54.502 --> 43:56.998
No place.
A dream place. Fuzzy.

43:57.033 --> 43:59.493
Are you planning on going bowling?

43:59.919 --> 44:01.940
Bowling? Did you hit your head?

44:01.975 --> 44:03.926
What are your plans tomorrow?

44:03.961 --> 44:07.250
Levanna's birthday is Sunday,
but tips are real good on a Sunday

44:07.285 --> 44:10.539
so I was gonna work it and celebrate
her birthday tomorrow instead.

44:11.170 --> 44:14.087
A lot of people died in that
dream of yours, huh Odd?

44:14.122 --> 44:15.331
Yeah, they did.

44:16.170 --> 44:17.828
Your dreams ever come true?

44:18.129 --> 44:19.704
Sometimes.

44:20.962 --> 44:22.206
I thought so.

44:24.171 --> 44:25.829
Close your eyes, Vi.

44:36.587 --> 44:40.203
In your dream what do you see?

44:40.838 --> 44:43.456
- What do you hear?
- All right.

44:44.379 --> 44:46.666
I'm running.

44:47.297 --> 44:51.456
There's suddenly lots of
flashing lights with...

44:52.214 --> 44:54.086
old-fashioned kiddie music.

44:56.672 --> 45:00.120
And then I hear a big crowd,
a roaring one.

45:01.173 --> 45:03.096
Like in a big football stadium.

45:03.131 --> 45:06.165
And then there's the sound
of water, gushing water.

45:07.631 --> 45:08.875
How do you die?

45:09.714 --> 45:13.127
It's like someone hit me with
a baseball bat, quick, like twice.

45:13.673 --> 45:16.381
I scream and
fall to my hands and knees.

45:16.416 --> 45:18.104
My hands slip, slippery.

45:18.139 --> 45:19.792
What are you slipping on?

45:20.215 --> 45:23.090
Oh, God. Blood.
There's blood everywhere.

45:23.125 --> 45:25.965
What's under the blood,
under your hands?

45:26.000 --> 45:27.899
A floor, grass, concrete?

45:27.934 --> 45:29.798
I'm staring at the dead man.

45:32.216 --> 45:35.131
Do you know him?
Do you recognize him?

45:39.716 --> 45:42.631
Oh, dear Lord, Odd.
So many dead bodies.

45:44.175 --> 45:46.663
Odd, you have to stop
this from happening.

45:51.175 --> 45:53.196
Oh, Odd, is there any hope
this could pass?

45:53.231 --> 45:55.217
If you listen to Oddie,
you'll be just fine.

45:55.251 --> 45:56.247
No.

45:57.508 --> 46:00.900
Fate is not a straight road.
There are many forks in it.

46:00.935 --> 46:04.292
You have the free will to choose
which one you take, but...

46:04.717 --> 46:06.141
sometimes it will bend around...

46:06.176 --> 46:09.588
and bring you straight back
to that same stubborn fate.

46:11.384 --> 46:13.126
I just wanna check on the girls.

46:18.468 --> 46:20.340
They're so beautiful, Viola.

46:21.052 --> 46:22.927
And they're such good girls.

46:22.962 --> 46:24.776
They're lucky to have you.

46:24.811 --> 46:26.591
That's what everyone says.

46:55.012 --> 46:56.174
Odd?

46:57.428 --> 46:59.715
- Anything wrong?
- No.

47:00.137 --> 47:04.096
No, no, no. I just wanted
to make sure the girls were safe.

47:04.131 --> 47:06.227
And with the bars on the windows

47:06.262 --> 47:09.095
I taught them how to work
the emergency release myself.

47:23.346 --> 47:27.720
Well, looks like everything's
a- okay in here.

47:29.597 --> 47:31.534
Step one, do not stay here.

47:31.569 --> 47:33.437
I'll go to my grandma's.

47:33.472 --> 47:34.618
Don't tell your grandma
you're coming.

47:34.653 --> 47:35.764
Don't tell the girls
where you're going.

47:35.799 --> 47:37.594
I don't want you overheard.

47:37.629 --> 47:39.354
- By who?
- By anyone.

47:39.389 --> 47:42.008
Or anything. Just go with it.

47:44.389 --> 47:47.921
Step two is don't go bowling if
for some reason you get the itch.

47:52.306 --> 47:54.181
I can't believe we're leaving
those horrid things...

47:54.216 --> 47:55.974
hovering around those sweet girls.

47:56.009 --> 47:56.855
They won't hurt em.

47:56.890 --> 47:58.974
They just want to smell em
before they die.

47:59.009 --> 48:00.106
God.

48:00.140 --> 48:03.348
Look, Stormy, there's nothing
I can do about bodachs, okay?

48:03.383 --> 48:05.188
And right now
I wouldn't even if I could.

48:05.223 --> 48:08.474
I need em to help me see the danger
coming so I can maybe prevent it.

48:08.509 --> 48:11.388
And when they eventually find out
that you can see them?

48:16.474 --> 48:17.898
Oddie, will you ever leave here?

48:17.933 --> 48:21.266
Well, I sure hope I don't end up like
Tom Jedd hanging out at Tire World.

48:21.301 --> 48:23.257
I meant while you're alive.

48:26.059 --> 48:28.515
Hey. Hey, Stormy.

48:28.550 --> 48:30.972
Hey, hey. Look, look.

48:33.059 --> 48:35.434
Look, Stormy,
if you want us to go, I'll go.

48:35.469 --> 48:36.891
It's not that. It's-

48:38.267 --> 48:40.423
I am just so scared for you, Oddie.

48:40.767 --> 48:44.180
So scared, ever since
I saw that creep Fungus Bob.

48:45.643 --> 48:47.099
I'm sorry. I just-

48:48.476 --> 48:50.217
I love you so much.

48:55.226 --> 48:56.650
My Pooh Bear.

48:56.685 --> 48:59.935
I promise you on
the other side of tomorrow...

48:59.970 --> 49:03.550
I will have all my stuffing intact.

49:08.477 --> 49:10.135
That must be for you.

49:57.229 --> 49:58.557
Oh, God!

49:59.605 --> 50:03.000
I heard the scream.
She ran across my yard.

50:03.035 --> 50:06.396
I saw the dogs following her.
I grabbed my gun.

50:07.647 --> 50:08.981
I shot the dogs.

50:09.015 --> 50:10.354
It's on.

50:12.856 --> 50:15.558
All right. Here's what we know.

50:16.189 --> 50:21.272
Lysette left my barbecue with
Officer Eckles at around 7:45.

50:21.307 --> 50:23.947
He dropped her off at home
clocked in at 8:00,

50:23.981 --> 50:26.690
and was manning the front
desk when he got the call.

50:26.725 --> 50:30.113
So somewhere
between 8:00 and midnight,

50:30.148 --> 50:32.753
Lysette was whacked in the eye
and then tied up

50:32.788 --> 50:35.357
and gagged and hauled
all the way the hell out here

50:35.392 --> 50:37.822
and had two Rottweilers
sicked on her.

50:37.857 --> 50:40.565
Hey, Chief. What's with
the guy who shot the dogs?

50:40.600 --> 50:42.197
His name's Kevin Goss.

50:42.232 --> 50:44.280
He was teaching a class
from 6:00 to 10:00...

50:44.315 --> 50:47.107
then he went to Starbucks
till they closed at midnight.

50:47.142 --> 50:49.513
He got home about
two minutes too late.

50:49.816 --> 50:53.691
Sir? I've actually seen
those Rottweilers before.

50:53.726 --> 50:55.563
They belong to Bob Robertson.

50:58.692 --> 51:00.148
All right!

51:00.567 --> 51:03.900
I want an A. P. B.
put out on this guy now!

51:03.935 --> 51:05.198
- Find him!
- Yes, sir.

51:05.233 --> 51:08.275
Simon, I want you to go back
over to Robertson's house.

51:08.310 --> 51:09.941
I'll have a search
warrant in the morning

51:09.976 --> 51:11.157
as soon as the courthouse opens.

51:11.192 --> 51:14.942
Sir, no offense, but I wasted most
of the day staking out that house.

51:14.977 --> 51:18.693
Then I went to the bowling alley
and stayed there untiI they closed.

51:18.728 --> 51:20.019
Nothing happened.

51:20.651 --> 51:23.270
Nobody showed.
It was a complete waste of my time.

51:23.901 --> 51:28.891
Sir, are we sure this Robertson
character isn't just a wild goose chase?

51:29.401 --> 51:31.401
Exactly where were you between
the hours of 8:00 and 10:00?

51:31.436 --> 51:35.146
- He was with me the whole time.
- Just ease up.

51:35.443 --> 51:38.485
Now go check the house again
and ask around about the dogs.

51:38.520 --> 51:39.813
Yes, sir.

51:42.027 --> 51:43.140
You two.

51:43.694 --> 51:44.808
Home.

51:45.444 --> 51:46.606
Go, now!

51:51.486 --> 51:55.646
I think you should wear this.
Try not to laugh.

52:03.903 --> 52:06.612
Oddie, you are not responsible
for every death you can't prevent.

52:06.647 --> 52:07.493
She died.

52:07.528 --> 52:10.570
And if Fungus Bob was her killer,
I was either slow or stupid.

52:10.605 --> 52:11.661
Choose your weapon.

52:11.696 --> 52:13.452
Why would Fungus Bob kill Lysette?

52:13.487 --> 52:15.202
What's the connection?
It makes no sense.

52:15.237 --> 52:19.529
It doesn't have to make sense.
It just has to satisfy some sick urge.

52:19.564 --> 52:21.401
Maybe he's warming up.

52:22.112 --> 52:24.946
I think the chief just sent
some detectives to protect you.

52:24.981 --> 52:26.688
I don't need protecting.

52:27.862 --> 52:30.979
Actually I think it might
just be surveillance.

52:31.904 --> 52:33.245
Fungus Bob followed me
to the church.

52:33.280 --> 52:35.863
I bet the chief is hoping
he'll sniff me out again.

52:35.898 --> 52:37.495
If the chief is using you as bait...

52:37.530 --> 52:40.647
he should at least ask if
you mind having a hook in your ass.

52:45.988 --> 52:49.818
Oh, man, I got to stay focused.

52:51.905 --> 52:54.821
Good. You keep an eye on my girl.

52:55.989 --> 52:57.861
August 15th had begun.

52:58.281 --> 53:00.022
Time was running out.

53:47.033 --> 53:48.491
Hey, Bob.

53:49.617 --> 53:51.489
You're not planning
on getting up, are ya?

53:55.368 --> 53:57.026
But if you're dead...

53:57.451 --> 53:59.939
who's gonna massacre Pico Mundo?

54:00.660 --> 54:03.693
Gun on the floor,
dead guy in my tub.

54:04.201 --> 54:06.488
I know a setup when I see one.

54:07.535 --> 54:10.867
But if I call the police,
the chief will have to arrest me...

54:10.902 --> 54:14.200
and I won't be able to stop
the catastrophe from happening.

54:24.411 --> 54:26.042
Oh, my God!

54:26.077 --> 54:28.282
Oh, you are creeping me out.

54:42.744 --> 54:44.617
You're freezing cold, Bob.

54:45.454 --> 54:48.368
Your rigor mortis is way advanced.

54:49.621 --> 54:51.611
You know...

54:51.828 --> 54:54.329
the chief said
you didn't leave any fingerprints.

54:54.364 --> 54:56.201
He didn't leave a single print.

54:58.079 --> 55:01.279
And Stormy never actually saw you.

55:02.121 --> 55:03.495
- Come on!
- What?

55:07.455 --> 55:09.476
Because you were already dead.

55:09.511 --> 55:11.462
And the whole time in the church,

55:11.497 --> 55:14.163
you were actually
a pissed-off poltergeist.

55:14.198 --> 55:16.795
I think the last time
I saw Fungus Bob alive...

55:16.830 --> 55:19.947
was when he left his house
right before I broke into it.

55:21.205 --> 55:25.205
He's been haunting me ever since,
blaming me for his death.

55:25.240 --> 55:29.206
Why he blames me or who the hell
killed him is a little hazy.

55:29.241 --> 55:31.928
If I'm caught,
I'll either be arrested for murder

55:31.963 --> 55:34.616
or rolling what looks like
the biggest joint ever.

55:51.707 --> 55:53.697
It's just me, Rosalia!

56:06.916 --> 56:08.907
Damn it.

56:10.375 --> 56:12.744
Oh, give me a break.

56:14.417 --> 56:16.905
It's just me, again, Rosalia.

56:18.375 --> 56:21.083
I'm gonna borrow
your car again, okay?

56:21.118 --> 56:22.424
If I'm being framed,

56:22.459 --> 56:25.309
why the police have failed
to arrive and arrest me...

56:25.344 --> 56:28.159
or the murderer hasn't come
to kill me, I do not know.

56:40.460 --> 56:43.958
All right, Bob, where can I put you
to quietly decompose for a while...

56:43.993 --> 56:47.457
before someone finds you and has
a new love of Jesus scared into em?

57:06.211 --> 57:07.842
Interesting story, Bob.

57:07.877 --> 57:10.794
After the federal government
abandoned this prison...

57:10.829 --> 57:13.135
it went through a long
series of owners.

57:13.170 --> 57:17.753
Rumor has it that at Von Zipper's
Burgers the fries were delicious...

57:17.788 --> 57:21.201
and the free-soft-drink-refill
policy was generously honored.

57:24.212 --> 57:26.677
And yet, this fine
dining establishment...

57:26.712 --> 57:31.504
never succeeded in winning
over the family-dining crowd...

57:31.539 --> 57:35.035
which is so essential
to any restaurant operation.

57:36.004 --> 57:38.136
Welcome to the gas chamber.

57:38.171 --> 57:39.837
A lot of people died in here, Bob.

57:39.872 --> 57:41.504
You should feeI right at home.

57:56.713 --> 58:00.464
Stormy's always joking about running
off to Las Vegas and getting married.

58:00.499 --> 58:03.506
But I tell her Vegas is packed
with dead people and bad guys...

58:03.540 --> 58:06.504
and I'd just end up
fighting eviI 24-7.

58:08.714 --> 58:10.788
I should have listened to her.

58:13.507 --> 58:14.619
Too many.

58:16.090 --> 58:17.748
Too many.

58:38.799 --> 58:40.556
The chief.

58:40.591 --> 58:41.918
I need the chief.

58:44.008 --> 58:45.764
Dear Lord.

58:45.799 --> 58:49.331
If that's you again, Odd,
we are going to have words!

59:01.009 --> 59:03.083
Oh, my God.

59:10.801 --> 59:12.984
No offense, Odd Thomas,
but I can't think of anybody...

59:13.019 --> 59:15.167
who could come in here right now
and not get my back up.

59:15.467 --> 59:17.822
- So you think he knew the shooter?
- Had to.

59:17.857 --> 59:20.177
Which means it's probably
somebody I know, too.

59:20.212 --> 59:22.665
- How bad is he?
- Bad.

59:24.219 --> 59:26.504
- Well, he's a fighter.
- He better be.

59:27.969 --> 59:29.946
- Hey, Bern.
- Ma'am.

59:29.981 --> 59:31.924
INTENSIVE CARE UNIT

59:34.136 --> 59:36.706
- Hey.
- Oh Oddie.

59:36.927 --> 59:39.969
Keep those reporters out of here.
You, on that door.

59:40.004 --> 59:42.256
- Sorry, no press inside.
- Comin through.

59:45.387 --> 59:47.342
You saved his life, Oddie.

59:48.387 --> 59:50.176
Where's this bullet?

59:50.678 --> 59:53.381
That's the one they're
trying to dig out of him now.

59:57.137 --> 59:59.128
Time is up.

59:59.346 --> 01:00:04.133
Pico Mundo is awakening
to a horror that only I can stop.

01:00:05.054 --> 01:00:07.304
Lysette and Fungus Bob are dead.

01:00:07.339 --> 01:00:09.519
The chief is
in the emergency room.

01:00:09.554 --> 01:00:12.470
There's hoards of bodachs
swarming all over town.

01:00:12.505 --> 01:00:14.186
Whatever's coming is gonna be big.

01:00:14.221 --> 01:00:16.894
I'm scared,
and I'm supposed to be fearless.

01:00:16.929 --> 01:00:19.117
- Don't tell me to stay home today.
- Please stay home today.

01:00:19.152 --> 01:00:21.305
- I will if you stay home with me.
- We've been through this.

01:00:21.340 --> 01:00:23.805
I have to do
whatever I can to stop it.

01:00:23.840 --> 01:00:25.770
Is Viola going to be shot dead?

01:00:25.805 --> 01:00:28.092
You know I don't know
that for sure.

01:00:28.513 --> 01:00:31.085
She's had it hard in life.
She doesn't need this.

01:00:31.722 --> 01:00:34.104
Shot dead? Really?
Who does need it?

01:00:34.139 --> 01:00:36.722
Oh, I don't know
why I try to reason with you.

01:00:36.757 --> 01:00:37.854
I always lose.

01:00:37.889 --> 01:00:39.910
You're a fabulous man of action,
odd one.

01:00:39.945 --> 01:00:41.931
You don't need to be
a good debater, too.

01:00:41.966 --> 01:00:43.687
Besides, you said yourself...

01:00:43.722 --> 01:00:46.431
any road I choose could lead me
right back to the same fate.

01:00:46.466 --> 01:00:48.598
So, which is it?
Do I have free will?

01:00:48.633 --> 01:00:50.257
Am I in God's hands?

01:00:51.098 --> 01:00:52.105
Or is it both?

01:00:52.140 --> 01:00:54.431
Have I ever told you
you've got a lot of issues?

01:00:54.466 --> 01:00:56.189
I'm a woman. We all have issues.

01:00:56.224 --> 01:00:59.286
It's what keeps us interesting,
and you men interested.

01:00:59.321 --> 01:01:02.348
Oh, yeah? It's what makes us
crazy and die younger.

01:01:02.383 --> 01:01:03.592
Do you love me?

01:01:04.348 --> 01:01:06.515
I love you more than life itself.

01:01:06.550 --> 01:01:09.347
See? It's working.

01:01:15.058 --> 01:01:17.891
Don't look back. Don't look back.

01:01:17.926 --> 01:01:19.135
Give him strength.

01:01:23.100 --> 01:01:24.557
Knock, knock.

01:01:29.558 --> 01:01:32.342
I'm hoping Bob left
a clue on his computer.

01:01:33.184 --> 01:01:35.589
Something to lead me
to his partner...

01:01:37.350 --> 01:01:40.059
to the person who was
planning on killing 100s,

01:01:40.094 --> 01:01:43.093
if not 1000s of people.

01:02:43.520 --> 01:02:44.527
Hey.

01:02:44.562 --> 01:02:46.312
Loop me in, odd one.
Where are you?

01:02:46.347 --> 01:02:48.201
I'm walking towards the fridge.

01:02:48.235 --> 01:02:50.054
Yours, mine, or Fungus Bob's?

01:02:51.646 --> 01:02:53.153
Don't "uh-huh" me. I told you...

01:02:53.188 --> 01:02:55.896
you are not allowed to go playing
around in any more hell gates.

01:02:55.931 --> 01:02:57.472
Next!

01:02:57.771 --> 01:03:00.121
Oh, God. Cockroaches.

01:03:00.156 --> 01:03:02.470
Always cockroaches.

01:03:02.688 --> 01:03:05.064
- Odd Thomas, did you hear me?
- Which part?

01:03:05.099 --> 01:03:06.278
I can't believe
you went back there.

01:03:06.313 --> 01:03:09.644
Every time you don't listen to me,
you get yourself into trouble.

01:03:10.189 --> 01:03:13.519
- I wish I'd listened to you.
- You get out of there right now.

01:03:13.814 --> 01:03:16.729
Right, right. Leaving. Leaving.

01:03:19.773 --> 01:03:22.481
Never heard you make that
sound before. Is everything okay?

01:03:22.516 --> 01:03:26.309
- Yeah.
- What are you looking at?

01:03:27.898 --> 01:03:28.905
Fingers.

01:03:28.940 --> 01:03:31.523
Please say they're attached
to someone's hand.

01:03:31.558 --> 01:03:32.738
Sorry.

01:03:32.773 --> 01:03:33.989
Get out of there, Oddie.

01:03:34.024 --> 01:03:37.238
Someone has been buying
a lot of Burke and Bailey's.

01:03:37.273 --> 01:03:39.440
Yeah? Well, you tell whoever's
buying it that our ice cream...

01:03:39.475 --> 01:03:42.059
may be the best,
but it'll still melt in hell.

01:03:43.941 --> 01:03:45.691
- I'm calling the police.
- No.

01:03:45.726 --> 01:03:46.935
No. Wait.

01:03:47.149 --> 01:03:49.566
I'll leave here first.
Then I'll call 'em.

01:03:49.601 --> 01:03:50.976
Be careful.

01:03:51.011 --> 01:03:52.351
Don't worry.

01:03:59.983 --> 01:04:01.226
Hey, Bob.

01:04:02.900 --> 01:04:05.657
I guess when I began to out you,
word somehow spread...

01:04:05.692 --> 01:04:11.108
and you became a liability to
your partner and he had to kill you.

01:04:11.525 --> 01:04:12.769
Sorry about that.

01:04:17.567 --> 01:04:22.275
I find it funny how I know more
about dead people than dead people.

01:04:22.310 --> 01:04:23.366
This is our realm, Bob.

01:04:23.401 --> 01:04:26.434
You can't physically harm
a living person.

01:04:30.902 --> 01:04:32.560
But there is that.

01:04:42.902 --> 01:04:45.473
Your call cannot be
completed as dialed.

01:04:54.152 --> 01:04:56.107
Gas.

01:05:24.571 --> 01:05:28.566
I'm exhausted, I'm lost,
and somewhere along the way...

01:05:28.601 --> 01:05:32.561
I missed an important clue
that could take me home.

01:05:37.488 --> 01:05:39.360
The bullet through the heart.

01:05:49.572 --> 01:05:51.859
It wasn't about the chief.

01:06:13.949 --> 01:06:16.235
God.

01:06:40.700 --> 01:06:44.030
Enough already, Bob. Please.

01:06:46.450 --> 01:06:50.278
My three least favorite words.

01:06:50.617 --> 01:06:52.359
Some..

01:06:54.784 --> 01:06:56.442
assembly...

01:06:56.659 --> 01:06:58.708
required.

01:06:58.743 --> 01:07:01.660
Simon, I've been dying to know
what that tattoo means.

01:07:01.695 --> 01:07:04.860
Let's just say this tattoo
is a crude obscenity.

01:07:06.952 --> 01:07:08.325
It's Varner.

01:07:09.034 --> 01:07:11.950
I once had a run-in with
some devil worshipers.

01:07:12.285 --> 01:07:13.743
I should've known.

01:07:15.410 --> 01:07:19.125
P- O-D. Prince Of Darkness.

01:07:19.160 --> 01:07:22.042
No wonder Varner was suspicious
when I told him...

01:07:22.077 --> 01:07:24.661
Fungus Bob had gotten aggressive
with me an hour earlier.

01:07:24.696 --> 01:07:27.908
This guy Bob Robertson
got aggressive with you?

01:07:28.119 --> 01:07:31.449
He had already killed Bob
5 or 6 hours before that.

01:07:31.745 --> 01:07:34.001
And that police van
protecting Stormy?

01:07:34.036 --> 01:07:36.328
That must've been Varner
waiting to follow me home...

01:07:36.363 --> 01:07:38.739
to bust me
for Fungus Bob's murder.

01:07:38.774 --> 01:07:41.114
Or shoot me while resisting arrest.

01:07:45.620 --> 01:07:47.877
There were no bodachs around Varner.

01:07:47.912 --> 01:07:50.669
But I can still feel myself
being drawn to him...

01:07:50.704 --> 01:07:54.235
and to the place where
he's about to commit mass murder.

01:07:54.871 --> 01:07:56.244
GREEN MOON MALL

01:08:02.371 --> 01:08:04.575
Coconut cherry chocolate chunk.

01:08:05.079 --> 01:08:07.153
Oh, God, no.

01:08:17.580 --> 01:08:19.156
POLICE

01:08:20.205 --> 01:08:22.080
Hey, Nell,
I see what the problem is.

01:08:22.115 --> 01:08:22.962
Stormy.

01:08:22.997 --> 01:08:25.912
You are eating and
reading at the same time.

01:08:25.948 --> 01:08:27.904
How about I eat and you read?

01:08:28.831 --> 01:08:32.279
No? Not so good? Okay, fine.

01:08:46.665 --> 01:08:50.196
All right, Varner, where are you?

01:09:28.417 --> 01:09:30.622
SECURITY

01:09:41.542 --> 01:09:44.660
Fungus Bob didn't just
have one kill buddy.

01:09:45.627 --> 01:09:46.841
He had two.

01:09:46.876 --> 01:09:50.917
One more, and they could buy group
health insurance or form a rock band.

01:09:50.953 --> 01:09:53.407
Officer Eckles is checking
that right now.

01:09:54.377 --> 01:09:56.252
I don't know what this
Odd Thomas character knows...

01:09:56.287 --> 01:09:57.936
but I know that Robertson
is stupid and careless...

01:09:57.971 --> 01:09:59.586
and he's gonna get us nailed
if we don't do something.

01:09:59.621 --> 01:10:00.467
Relax.

01:10:00.502 --> 01:10:03.835
Did Robertson ever find those
photos at the mall he misplaced?

01:10:03.870 --> 01:10:08.328
I said, relax.
I'll take care of him.

01:10:19.794 --> 01:10:22.284
Stalking someone at the mall, Bern?

01:10:22.920 --> 01:10:24.579
Robertson, that idiot.

01:10:27.087 --> 01:10:28.962
We got to make it
look like an accident.

01:10:28.997 --> 01:10:31.102
Oh, it'll look like
an accident all right.

01:10:31.137 --> 01:10:33.207
When I find Robertson,
I'm gonna kill him.

01:10:33.546 --> 01:10:35.702
Already been there, done that.

01:10:41.546 --> 01:10:44.879
Looks like their plan was to jump
out at the end of the mall disaster

01:10:44.914 --> 01:10:47.499
like heroes responding to the call.

01:10:48.338 --> 01:10:52.166
But I never saw any bodachs
around Eckles, either.

01:10:52.505 --> 01:10:56.501
The presence of the bodachs
tipped me off to Fungus Bob...

01:10:56.536 --> 01:11:00.498
but not to his two co-conspirators,
which now seems...

01:11:00.838 --> 01:11:02.346
intentional.

01:11:02.381 --> 01:11:06.540
As if the bodachs knew of my gift,
as if they know I can see them.

01:11:07.922 --> 01:11:10.494
The bodachs have been
manipulating me.

01:11:32.090 --> 01:11:34.046
I'm gonna finish you off,
old man.

01:11:38.633 --> 01:11:39.847
Four.

01:11:39.882 --> 01:11:42.169
Well, that's just jiffy.

01:12:13.551 --> 01:12:16.667
This just so happens
to be my very favorite book.

01:12:17.301 --> 01:12:19.458
The Wonderful Wizard Of Oz.

01:12:19.676 --> 01:12:25.010
Officer Varner Prince of Darkness,
Officer Varner, Prince of Darkness.

01:12:35.094 --> 01:12:36.255
Viola.

01:12:36.469 --> 01:12:38.594
- Viola! What are you doing here?
- Odd! Geez!

01:12:38.629 --> 01:12:40.684
- You scared the-
- What are you doing here?

01:12:40.719 --> 01:12:42.656
We had to pick out
a birthday present for Levanna.

01:12:42.691 --> 01:12:45.142
And Nicolina wanted to get
a card for her big sister.

01:12:45.177 --> 01:12:47.593
Look, your dream, it's happening
right here, right now.

01:12:48.220 --> 01:12:50.990
I thought in a big stadium or
at the water park or a bowling alley.

01:12:51.025 --> 01:12:53.761
Ladies, I need you to take Viola
and get her out of here, okay?

01:12:53.796 --> 01:12:56.464
Come on.
Come on, come on. Go on.

01:12:57.720 --> 01:12:59.561
This made Dorothy so very angry...

01:12:59.596 --> 01:13:01.887
that she picked up the bucket
of water that stood near...

01:13:01.922 --> 01:13:04.590
and dashed it all over
the wicked witch.

01:13:05.512 --> 01:13:08.006
And then the wicked witch said...

01:13:08.041 --> 01:13:10.502
"I'm melting! I'm melting!"

01:13:13.346 --> 01:13:15.917
There's suddenly lots
of flashing lights.

01:13:16.263 --> 01:13:18.833
With old-fashioned kiddie music.

01:13:21.055 --> 01:13:23.010
And then I hear a big crowd.

01:13:25.430 --> 01:13:28.630
And then there's the sound of water,
gushing water.

01:13:32.097 --> 01:13:33.758
Bye, Nell.

01:13:33.793 --> 01:13:35.421
Bye, Stormy.

01:13:37.722 --> 01:13:39.597
Excuse me. Excuse me. Sorry!

01:13:39.632 --> 01:13:41.138
Move, move. Excuse me!

01:14:29.475 --> 01:14:32.177
A gun! He's got a gun!

01:15:25.228 --> 01:15:28.759
Stormy and I are destined
to be together forever.

01:15:29.603 --> 01:15:33.549
Gypsy Mummy gave us a card that
said so, for a single quarter...

01:15:34.187 --> 01:15:36.675
what other couples couldn't
buy at any price.

01:15:40.728 --> 01:15:42.388
No!

01:16:06.272 --> 01:16:08.760
Get out of the way! Get off!

01:17:11.567 --> 01:17:13.024
Hi.

01:17:24.400 --> 01:17:25.728
Odd!

01:17:33.359 --> 01:17:34.687
Odd!

01:17:36.152 --> 01:17:37.728
It's not over.

01:17:44.194 --> 01:17:45.520
It's not over.

01:17:46.152 --> 01:17:48.771
It's not over. It's not over.

01:17:51.694 --> 01:17:54.069
Hey Chief. What's with
the guy who shot the dogs?

01:17:54.104 --> 01:17:56.355
His names Kevin Goss.

01:17:56.778 --> 01:17:58.653
One of these days, bang!

01:17:58.688 --> 01:17:59.814
You hear me?

01:18:21.570 --> 01:18:24.485
He's got a gun!

01:18:39.405 --> 01:18:41.037
- Is this your truck?
- I need a drill!

01:18:41.072 --> 01:18:42.884
Do you have a drill?
I need to get this open!

01:18:42.919 --> 01:18:44.662
- Who the hell are you?
- I'm a cop. Now look!

01:18:44.697 --> 01:18:46.780
You see that woman?
Some maniacs just shot up the mall!

01:18:46.815 --> 01:18:49.072
So either get with me,
get behind me, or get out!

01:18:49.107 --> 01:18:50.648
I got a grinder!

01:19:02.322 --> 01:19:04.812
Oh, my God.

01:19:20.866 --> 01:19:23.782
Everyone get the hell out of here!
Get the hell out!

01:19:23.817 --> 01:19:24.896
Now!

01:20:12.119 --> 01:20:13.231
Hey!

01:20:34.286 --> 01:20:35.530
Shit!

01:20:45.245 --> 01:20:47.947
You really set yourself up, asshole!

01:21:27.122 --> 01:21:29.825
It's cold in the desert.

01:22:16.083 --> 01:22:19.416
I could tell my stuffing
wasn't entirely intact.

01:22:19.451 --> 01:22:21.340
He's awake. He's awake!

01:22:21.375 --> 01:22:24.207
But it was nothing
they couldn't stitch back together.

01:22:31.083 --> 01:22:33.793
Karla told me that the chief
had come through just fine...

01:22:33.828 --> 01:22:36.466
and somehow managed
to spin Fungus Bob's corpse...

01:22:36.501 --> 01:22:40.115
into a bizarre cover story
that kept my secret a secret.

01:22:45.126 --> 01:22:47.300
An FBI expert
on television said that

01:22:47.335 --> 01:22:50.251
if you hadn't gotten
those explosives out of there,

01:22:50.286 --> 01:22:53.133
at least 500 or 600 people
would've died, for sure.

01:22:53.168 --> 01:22:57.114
They told me events at the Green Moon
Mall had made headlines everywhere.

01:22:58.168 --> 01:23:00.658
But I didn't want to read
or see anything about it.

01:23:02.335 --> 01:23:03.217
According to Eckles...

01:23:03.252 --> 01:23:06.440
he and Varner started a satanic
cult when they were teenagers.

01:23:06.475 --> 01:23:09.628
One night, they killed a man
and realized they enjoyed it.

01:23:09.663 --> 01:23:10.927
So they kept at it,

01:23:10.962 --> 01:23:13.876
eventually joining
the police force for better cover.

01:23:14.920 --> 01:23:18.103
They met Robertson and Goss
and came up with a plan...

01:23:18.138 --> 01:23:21.287
to infiltrate a small town
and then slowly kill it.

01:23:32.754 --> 01:23:34.177
Odd! Odd! Odd!

01:23:34.212 --> 01:23:36.701
Detail, present arms.

01:23:37.546 --> 01:23:38.427
ODD SAVES

01:23:38.462 --> 01:23:39.629
MARRY ME ODD!
ODD WORLD

01:23:39.664 --> 01:23:41.786
IN ODD WE TRUST

01:24:02.547 --> 01:24:03.554
When I'm with you,

01:24:03.589 --> 01:24:07.334
I don't have to worry about
pancakes or poltergeists.

01:24:08.381 --> 01:24:11.711
When I'm with you,
I'm with my destiny.

01:24:12.548 --> 01:24:16.162
Where you live, I flourish.

01:24:21.173 --> 01:24:23.662
We ate food that wasn't healthy.

01:24:26.382 --> 01:24:28.871
We drank too much...

01:24:30.549 --> 01:24:32.207
and slept too much...

01:24:38.674 --> 01:24:41.507
but could never kiss enough.

01:24:42.216 --> 01:24:45.048
Everything was just as I wished.

01:24:49.508 --> 01:24:53.668
- Yeah?
- Odd, it's us. Open up.

01:24:55.258 --> 01:24:57.592
- Hey, guys.
- We have been calling you, Oddie.

01:24:57.627 --> 01:24:59.891
I know. You know,
I disconnected the phone...

01:24:59.925 --> 01:25:02.217
because the reporters won't
leave me and Stormy alone.

01:25:02.252 --> 01:25:04.006
- Son.
- Do you want some-

01:25:06.509 --> 01:25:08.797
You've been here long enough.

01:25:08.832 --> 01:25:11.084
We think it's time to stop.

01:25:11.593 --> 01:25:16.499
Sweetheart, the coroner finally
released her poor body.

01:25:33.885 --> 01:25:35.675
A part of me knew...

01:25:36.302 --> 01:25:39.834
from the moment I saw her
behind the ice cream counter.

01:25:40.553 --> 01:25:43.385
But the truth hurt
too much to accept.

01:25:44.511 --> 01:25:47.842
Her death would have been
one wound too many that day.

01:25:49.011 --> 01:25:52.543
And I think I would have
let go of this life.

01:26:04.429 --> 01:26:06.384
She's here, isn't she?

01:26:13.596 --> 01:26:15.254
You got to let her go.

01:26:16.513 --> 01:26:19.427
She deserves to move
to her next life.

01:26:20.680 --> 01:26:22.006
Son...

01:26:24.013 --> 01:26:25.554
it's just time.

01:27:22.141 --> 01:27:23.599
I love you.

01:27:26.183 --> 01:27:30.343
I promise I will see you again.
Okay?

01:28:39.020 --> 01:28:43.575
YOU ARE NOW LEAVING PICO MUNDO
COME BACK AGAIN SOON

01:28:50.563 --> 01:28:53.605
Stormy always believed that life
is not about how fast you run...

01:28:53.640 --> 01:28:55.760
or with what degree of grace.

01:28:56.313 --> 01:28:58.361
That this life is a boot camp,

01:28:58.396 --> 01:29:00.936
that we must persevere
through all the obstacles

01:29:00.971 --> 01:29:03.478
and hardships to earn our way
into the next life.

01:29:04.522 --> 01:29:07.768
To be with her again, I will have
the perseverance of a bulldog.

01:29:09.230 --> 01:29:12.347
But sometimes, it seems to me...

01:29:13.189 --> 01:29:16.306
the training
is unnecessarily painful.

01:29:23.606 --> 01:29:25.654
If I live an average life-span...

01:29:25.689 --> 01:29:29.020
I'll have another 60 years
before I see Stormy again.

01:29:29.523 --> 01:29:31.313
That will be a long wait.

01:29:33.398 --> 01:29:35.354
But I am a patient man.

01:29:37.773 --> 01:29:40.060
And I have much to do.

